<br>
If someone buys your friend's car and avoids paying tax on the purchase by declaring it as a &quot;gift&quot;, do you feel uncomfortable driving when you see it on the road with someone else behind the wheel?  When someone who sits next to you at the soccer game sells his/her season tickets to someone one else, do you feel uncomfortable when you get to the game and see the other person sitting there?  If I were to let someone use my credit card, would you feel uncomfortable using a credit card issued by the same company?<br>
<br>
All of the above mentioned things are against &quot;the rules&quot; and all of them are fairly common occurances, yet I rarely see anyone besides authorities getting up-in-arms about any of them.  Selling a car without paying tax (in the US) is a violation of the law, selling tickets to a sporting event can be called &quot;scalping&quot; which is against the law in alot of states, and using someone's account at any kind of business is technically identity theft (federal offense). <br>
<br>
In what way does knowing a character was ebayed/given/traded/sold make you uncomfortable playing the game?  If you're grouped with one, and they suck, you leave the group!  Who really cares?  <br>
<br>
I think it's time we got off the ebay high horse, it happens.  It's going to keep happening.  Getting &quot;uncomfortable&quot; about it ruins who's gameplay?  Nobody's but yours.  *shrug*  If you want to self-impose stress into your virtual life, be my guest, but it sure seems that your behaviour is as rediculous as the people you're pointing a finger at.<br>
<br>
Love ya, T.. I really do, but being neurotic about ebayed toons is going a little over the edge <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
