 to be encouraged while discouraging the trade of money (RL time and talent are used here) for in game plat.<br>
<br>
Stavenham V, you are simply looking at this from two directions at once and confusing them.  It is not in question that the sale of plat is contrary to the EULA.  What is in question is the difference in purchasing it for RL money (the result of work) or goods/services (the result of work/work itself).<br>
<br>
As far as the rest of this goes, I judge people by how they act at the time that I meet them.  I get my first impression of them and try to give them the benefit of the doubt.  I try to forgive wrongs as quickly as I can and move on with my life.  I do not actively condone the breaking of rules, but I also won't hold it against anyone should I discover that they did so.  <br>
<br>
What matters most to me in this game is the &quot;now.&quot;  <br>
<br>
The reason we all come to Norrath is to have fun.  We enjoy what we do.  Some of us find the hunt the most enjoyable aspect.  Some of us are social magnets and spend the time making friends.  Some of us are after continual challenge.  Some of us enjoy the accomplishment of defeating the next creature.  Some of us just want to be the most powerful people around.  And some of us just want to be wealthy.<br>
<br>
There are so many aspects to this game to enjoy that it caters to a great variety of people.  Some don't want to spend a year to get a character up to level 60 with all of his skills maxxed, a GM in a tradeskill or two, an epic, and nice equipment.  <br>
<br>
Is it anti-roleplay to do so?  No.  I've run many high level D&amp;D campaigns where everyone started at level 25 so we could experience something new.  The players just had to make up a story for how they got up to where they were for background.  It has nothing to do with role-play.  There are many valid role-play ways you can explain the transferral of a character from one player to another.<br>
<br>
The way I see it, Sony is too concerned with making money to enforce that aspect of the EULA.  The agreement is with Sony and the individual players.  The agreement is not with the individual players and each and every one of us.  Our complaints here on this subject do no good.  Sony does not read this board and make their legal decisions based upon our complaints.<br>
<br>
I suggest we all live and let live...or better said, play and let play.  Remember that we are all here in Norrath to enjoy ourselves.  We all enjoy different things.  The GMs enforce what rules they see as important, so those who KS, ninja loot, and train intentionally are punished, while those who are seeking enjoyment from the game in a non-destructive manner are allowed to play as they wish. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=teiraa>teiraa</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/p/Groups/38/38498/folders/25939/182645blueheart5.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Innoruuk also needs love</span><br>  Posts: 462<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/2/03 3:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=67>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ebay Guilds (the post that will give you fuckers a clue)</span><hr size=1> Seems you got my point wrong. Look at my second post.<br>
